headline: Raymond James Earnings Beat Estimates on Investment Banking Boost
summary: Raymond James Financial  handily beat Wall Street’s expectations with its latest quarterly results, which benefited from a surge in investment banking revenue.  Raymond James shares fell 0.7% Thursday morning compared with 0.3% gain for the S&P 500.  “Despite some seasonal headwinds, we are optimistic entering the fiscal second quarter with strong client asset levels, solid loan growth and healthy activity levels for both financial advisor recruiting and investment banking,” CEO Paul Reilly said in a statement.
